<%# locals: event, user_rsvp — the optional line to the host.

    The only part of the RSVP block a turbo stream replaces, so it needs a
    stable id AND must render even with no RSVP: a target that only exists once
    somebody has answered can't be replaced on the answer that creates it, and
    the note would never appear without a reload (the same trap the attendee
    list had).

    Folded away until wanted: it sat permanently open before, competing with
    the RSVP itself for a field most people never fill in. <details> keeps that
    working without JavaScript. %>
<div id="rsvp-note-region" class="text-sm sm:text-right">
  <% if user_rsvp %>
    <details <%= "open" if user_rsvp.note.present? %>>
      <summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-cream/50 transition hover:text-cream/80 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
        <%= user_rsvp.note.present? ? "Your note to the host" : "Add a note for the host" %>
      </summary>
      <%= form_with url: event_event_rsvp_path(event, user_rsvp), method: :patch, local: true,
                    class: "mt-2 flex items-center gap-2 sm:justify-end" do |f| %>
        <label for="rsvp-note" class="sr-only">Note for the host</label>
        <input type="text" name="event_rsvp[note]" id="rsvp-note" maxlength="300"
               value="<%= user_rsvp.note %>" placeholder="Bringing a bottle, running late…"
               class="w-56 rounded-lg border border-cream/20 bg-cream/5 px-3 py-1.5 text-sm text-cream placeholder-cream/40 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-whiskey-400">
        <%= f.submit user_rsvp.note.present? ? "Update" : "Send",
            class: "cursor-pointer rounded-lg border border-cream/20 px-3 py-1.5 text-sm font-semibold text-cream/80 transition hover:bg-cream/10 hover:text-cream" %>
      <% end %>
    </details>
  <% end %>
</div>
